Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @Carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and
thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

== Pistachio Rice ==

Melt @Butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites;
cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @Jasmine Rice{½%cup}, ¾ cup water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil,
then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.
Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> 4 SERVINGS: Melt 2 TBSP butter. Use 1 1/2 cups water.

== Roasted Carrots ==

While rice cooks, toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of
@Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}; season with salt and @Pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Remove from oven and toss with lemon zest to taste.

== Salmon ==

Meanwhile, pat @Wild Sockeye Salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season
with salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add salmon skin sides down and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.
Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wash out pan.

== Sauce ==

Heat pan used for salmon over medium heat. Add @Seafood Stock Concentrate{1},
@Apricot Jam{2%tablespoon}, @Dried Apricots{1%ounce}, and ¼ cup water; stir to combine.
Season with a pinch of @Ancho Chili Powder{1%teaspoon} to taste (start with ¼ tsp
and add more from there if you like) and a squeeze of lemon juice to taste.

Simmer until mixture is thickened and glossy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat and
stir in @Butter{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Add more chili powder and
lemon juice if desired.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 1/3 cup water and 2 TBSP butter.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Pistachios{½%ounce} and half the scallion greens.
Season with salt and pepper.

Divide rice and carrots between plates. Serve salmon over rice. Top salmon with sauce
and garnish with remaining scallion greens. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges
on the side.